HEADWORD: Flysch
<hw>Flysch</hw> <pr>(fl⟦emac⟧sh)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[A Swiss word,
fr. G. <ets>fliessen</ets> to flow, melt.]</ety> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>
<def>A name given to the series of sandstones and schists overlying the
true nummulitic formation in the Alps, and included in the Eocene
Tertiary.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

